The smallest positive integer \( n \) from the options that contains the digit **9** and makes \(\frac{1}{n}\) a terminating decimal is **8192**.

\boxed{I}

**Explanation:** Terminating decimals occur when \( n \) has no prime factors other than 2 or 5. Among the options, only **8192** (which is \(2^{13}\)) contains the digit **9** and satisfies the condition.
